<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1146] rerunFailingTestsCount not working with Parameterized test</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1146</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I want to use the new feature to rerun failing tests implemented with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1087&quot; title=&quot;New option rerunFailingTestsCount&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1087&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-1087&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I can get it working with standard JUnit tests but it does not seem to do anything when using it in a Parameterized test. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To rule out that the custom JUnit runner I use is the cause, I created a sample project that only uses out of the box JUnit. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although it is easy to reproduce without doing anything special I attached the sample project.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
